  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nI've noticed that, when sending multiple messages, the last message has always an additional indentation that is not expected.\r\nThis changes with every next message sent (by the same logged-in user)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<img width=\"591\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-11-30 at 12 01 42\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/144035873-8ab53d4a-74b1-46d0-b767-70ee9b1793e9.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"602\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-11-30 at 12 01 52\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/144035842-46c9d510-6585-4dcb-9ecc-61dfb3d8e18c.png\">\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Log into Status, open community channel\r\n2. Send a message, then send another one\r\n3. The last message should have indentation\r\n4. Send yet another message, notice how the second to last message restored its indentation while the new last message has the indentation now\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo weird indentation when sending messages. (or indentation for all messages as stated in comment below)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nWeird indentation.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-11-30 at 15 13 25\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/82375995/144045579-7d3c9175-026b-47e2-85d3-f5867d0a9859.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1440\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-11-30 at 15 13 59\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/82375995/144045595-71d90c6a-651c-48b1-8620-00fa49012d4e.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n**NOTE**: it is gone when switching back and forth \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: `4d7d2261a` (latest `master` at the time of creating this issue)\r\n- Operating System: macOS 10.15.3\r\n\r\n",
